    "registeredDate": "2026-07-12",
    "rationale": "AMBER when the 80% time horizon reaches 40 hours. Verification cost does not scale with task length, so leverage is roughly (horizon x reliability) / (fixed oversight + rework). At 16h/80% a human still touches the work every other day; at 40h/80% the touch interval goes weekly and oversight becomes small relative to output. Arbitrary but fixed in advance and dated, so it cannot be renegotiated once the number arrives."
  },
