  "notes": [
    "50% reliability is a coin flip, not competence; the 80% horizon is roughly a fifth as long.",
    "Tasks are clean, self-contained, auto-scorable software/ML/cyber problems, not messy jobs.",
    "Human baselines are contractors with no prior context, not high-context professionals, so a '16-hour task' is not two days of anyone's actual job.",
    "Measurements above 16h are off the end of METR's ruler: only 5 of 228 tasks are >= 16h.",
    "METR corrected a regularization error on 2026-03-03 that pulled long horizons down; values still tagged pre_2026_03_03 carry roughly +/-15%.",
    "16h is a property of METR's instrument (a data-quality band), NOT the pre-registered threshold. The threshold is 40h at 80%."
  ],
